		<td><b>Justifying this hobby?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My cousin and I are members of this forum, both working on (separate) side-scroller engines. But we're under increasing pressure to justify our hobby to other family members who see us as "sitting and playing on the computer all day and not doing anything productive". I know NES games don't sell, but what marketable skill can one build by programming for the NES?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


