		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Try making them understand that they don't understand your hobby. Tell them it's a complex combination of designing, programming, problem solving, drawing, composing, ...
<br />
<br />Someone that doesn't know what it implies to write a book, or solve a big mathematical problem, would think the same as those family members.
<br />
<br />And, you don't need to justify your hobby. Your hobby is yours. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
