s in 6502 asm for NES, C + Allegro, Z80 asm for his TI calculator, various Lego robotics environments, Golly (2D cellular automata engine), RPG Maker 2 (for PlayStation 2), and some platforms I can't remember. He also edits old animated TV shows together in various dadaist or dirty ways. But he appears unproductive in part because he doesn't ship. He just doesn't think taking projects to completion is worth his effort.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">So maybe you should try to explain it to them and when they don't understand because it is too complicated maybe they'll STFU.</div>
